{"type":"text","timestamp":1775899566932,"sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdcdf5e001AB5ghPbDKKkUHz","messageID":"msg_d7bdcc7f3001h2Ih4B9mPRqnVs","sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context I need. I'll create the delta-spec.md file for AR-026 with comprehensive GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for the K8s/AgentCube Provider.","time":{"start":1775899566929,"end":1775899566929}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775899709891,"sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdd93c1001od8K6oyg51lX9m","messageID":"msg_d7bdcc7f3001h2Ih4B9mPRqnVs","sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","type":"text","text":" Scenario","time":{"start":1775899709888,"end":1775899709888}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899709915,"sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdce354001aMhIQ6gnGRw7zi","messageID":"msg_d7bdcc7f3001h2Ih4B9mPRqnVs","sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-026  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with default namespace\n- **GIVEN** no namespace is provided\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL default `namespace` to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with custom namespace\n- **GIVEN** `namespace=\"my-namespace\"`, `verbose=True`, and `kubeconfig=\"/path/to/kubeconfig\"`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(...)` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL store these values and configure the Kubernetes client accordingly\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with kubeconfig from environment\n- **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is `None` and environment variable `KUBECONFIG` is set\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the kubernetes client with default configuration (likely from `~/.kube/config` or in-cluster config)\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging during initialization\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(verbose=True)` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL log initialization details including namespace configuration\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Namespace Management\n\nThe system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before deploying resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n- **GIVEN** the namespace `\"my-namespace\"` already exists in the cluster\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL not raise an error and continue without creating the namespace again\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace does not exist\n- **GIVEN** the namespace `\"new-namespace\"` does not exist in the cluster\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL create the namespace using the Kubernetes API\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace creation failure\n- **GIVEN** the user lacks permission to create namespaces\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` attempts to create a namespace\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `ApiException` or permission error)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Name Sanitization\n\nThe system SHALL sanitize agent names to comply with Kubernetes resource naming conventions.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid name passed through\n- **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my-agent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` unchanged\n\n#### Scenario: Uppercase letters converted to lowercase\n- **GIVEN** an agent name `\"My-Agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"My-Agent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` (lowercase)\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid characters replaced\n- **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my_agent@v1.0\"`\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my_agent@v1.0\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a sanitized version with invalid characters replaced or removed\n\n#### Scenario: Long names truncated\n- **GIVEN** an agent name exceeding 63 characters (Kubernetes DNS label limit)\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL truncate the name to comply with Kubernetes naming constraints\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL deploy agents as Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy agent with minimal configuration\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"hello-agent\"`, `image_url=\"hello:v1.0.0\"`, `port=8080`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  1. Ensure namespace exists\n  2. Create a Deployment with the specified image and port\n  3. Create a NodePort Service exposing the port\n  4. Return deployment info including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy agent with custom entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python /app/main.py\"` and other required parameters\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the Deployment SHALL include the entrypoint as the container command\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy agent with multiple replicas\n- **GIVEN** `replicas=3` and other required parameters\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the Deployment SHALL specify `replicas: 3`\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy agent with specific NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port=30080` (within valid range 30000-32767)\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL use the specified NodePort, and `service_url` SHALL be `\"http://localhost:30080\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy agent with auto-assigned NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port=None`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL auto-assign a NodePort in range 30000-32767, and the returned `service_url` SHALL reflect the assigned port\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy agent with environment variables\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"LOG_LEVEL\": \"debug\", \"ENV\": \"production\"}`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the Deployment container SHALL include the specified environment variables\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy when Deployment already exists\n- **GIVEN** a Deployment with the same name already exists\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL update/patch the existing Deployment with new configuration (e.g., new image)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Deployment Resource Creation\n\nThe system SHALL create properly configured Kubernetes Deployment resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Create deployment with defaults\n- **GIVEN** minimal required parameters\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment(name, image_url, port, None, 1, None)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Deployment configuration dict with:\n  - `apiVersion: apps/v1`\n  - `kind: Deployment`\n  - Proper selector labels matching the agent name\n  - Container specification with the image and port\n\n#### Scenario: Create deployment with entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the container spec SHALL include `\"command\": [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Create deployment with replicas\n- **GIVEN** `replicas=5`\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the spec SHALL include `\"replicas\": 5`\n\n#### Scenario: Create deployment with env vars\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"KEY\": \"value\"}`\n- **WHEN** `_create_deployment(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the container spec SHALL include `\"env\": [{\"name\": \"KEY\", \"value\": \"value\"}]`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Service Resource Creation\n\nThe system SHALL create properly configured Kubernetes NodePort Service resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Create service with specific NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `port=8080`, `node_port=30080`\n- **WHEN** `_create_service(name=\"my-agent\", port=8080, node_port=30080)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Service configuration with:\n  - `type: NodePort`\n  - `ports` containing `port`, `targetPort`, and `nodePort`\n  - Selector matching the Deployment labels\n\n#### Scenario: Create service with auto-assigned NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port=None`\n- **WHEN** `_create_service(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the service spec SHALL omit `nodePort`, allowing Kubernetes to auto-assign\n\n#### Scenario: Service selector matches deployment\n- **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `_create_service(\"my-agent\", ...)` is called\n- **THEN** the service selector SHALL match the labels on the deployment pods\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Deployment Readiness Waiting\n\nThe system SHALL wait for deployments to become ready before considering them available.\n\n#### Scenario: Wait for deployment succeeds\n- **GIVEN** a deployment that becomes ready within timeout\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return without error once all replicas are ready\n\n#### Scenario: Wait for deployment times out\n- **GIVEN** a deployment that fails to become ready (e.g., image pull failure)\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError` after 120 seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout value\n- **GIVEN** `timeout=60`\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL wait up to 60 seconds before raising `TimeoutError`\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging during wait\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready()` executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL log status updates including replica counts and readiness status\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Status Retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve the current status of deployed agents.\n\n#### Scenario: Get status for running agent\n- **GIVEN** a running Deployment with available replicas\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return status dict including `status` (e.g., \"running\"), `replicas`, `available_replicas`, and `service_url`\n\n#### Scenario: Get status for non-existent agent\n- **GIVEN** no Deployment exists for the agent name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name=\"missing-agent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a status indicating the agent is not found (e.g., `status=\"not_found\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: Get status for scaling deployment\n- **GIVEN** a Deployment currently scaling (e.g., rolling update in progress)\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_status(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return status indicating the current state (e.g., `status=\"scaling\"` or show replica mismatch)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Deletion\n\nThe system SHALL properly delete deployed agents and their associated resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete existing agent\n- **GIVEN** an agent with existing Deployment and Service\n- **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL delete both the Deployment and Service, and return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": \"my-agent\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete non-existent agent (idempotent)\n- **GIVEN** no resources exist for the agent name\n- **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name=\"missing-agent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL ignore the 404 errors and return deletion confirmation\n\n#### Scenario: Delete agent with specific namespace\n- **GIVEN** an agent deployed in namespace `\"production\"`\n- **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is called on a provider initialized with `namespace=\"production\"`\n- **THEN** it SHALL delete resources from the correct namespace\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL provide `AgentCubeProvider` to deploy agents using the AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with defaults\n- **GIVEN** no parameters provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider()` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL default `namespace` to `\"default\"` and `verbose` to `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with custom parameters\n- **GIVEN** `namespace=\"agentcube-system\"`, `verbose=True`, `kubeconfig=None`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider(...)` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL store these configuration values\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL deploy agents as AgentRuntime Custom Resources for the AgentCube platform.\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with minimal configuration\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"my-runtime\"`, `image_url=\"myimage:v1.0\"`, `port=8080`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR in the configured namespace and return deployment info\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with readiness probe\n- **GIVEN** `readiness_probe_path=\"/health\"` and `readiness_probe_port=8080`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include readiness probe configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with environment variables from URLs\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"`, `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"`, and `env_vars=None`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variables automatically\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with custom env vars and URLs\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars={\"CUSTOM\": \"value\"}`, `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the resulting env SHALL contain both custom vars and the auto-injected WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with default timeout settings\n- **GIVEN** no session timeout parameters provided\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with image pull secrets\n- **GIVEN** any valid deployment parameters\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include `imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime with entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `entrypoint=\"python /app/server.py\"`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** the CR spec SHALL include the entrypoint in the container configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Update existing AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR with the same name already exists\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(...)` is called with a different image\n- **THEN** it SHALL patch/update the existing CR with the new configuration\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR Retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve AgentRuntime Custom Resources by name and namespace.\n\n#### Scenario: Get existing AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR named `\"my-runtime\"` exists in namespace `\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name=\"my-runtime\", namespace=\"default\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the CR object as a dict\n\n#### Scenario: Get non-existent AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists with the specified name\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name=\"missing-runtime\", namespace=\"default\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime with custom API group\n- **GIVEN** the CRD is defined for `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n- **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the correct API group/version when calling the Kubernetes API\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — Namespace Management\n\nThe system SHALL ensure namespace exists before deploying AgentRuntime CRs.\n\n#### Scenario: Ensure namespace for AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** the target namespace does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL create the namespace using Kubernetes API\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace already exists for AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** the target namespace exists\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL proceed without error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — Name Sanitization\n\nThe system SHALL sanitize names for AgentRuntime CRs using the same logic as KubernetesProvider.\n\n#### Scenario: Sanitize AgentRuntime name\n- **GIVEN** an agent name `\"My_Runtime@Prod\"`\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"My_Runtime@Prod\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Kubernetes-compliant name (lowercase, valid characters only)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Integration — PublishRuntime Provider Selection\n\nThe system SHALL use the appropriate provider based on the `provider` parameter.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish with K8s provider\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` in CLI or runtime options\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` to deploy the agent\n\n#### Scenario: Publish with AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` in CLI or runtime options\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` to deploy the AgentRuntime CR\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid provider raises error\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"invalid-provider\"`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime` attempts to deploy\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating invalid provider\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Integration — PublishRuntime Prerequisites\n\nThe system SHALL validate prerequisites before deploying with AgentCube provider.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider requires router_url and workload_manager_url\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s provider does not require AgentCube URLs\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and metadata has no `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL proceed with deployment without requiring these fields\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Integration — StatusRuntime Provider Selection\n\nThe system SHALL support status retrieval for both provider types.\n\n#### Scenario: Status for K8s deployment\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and agent was deployed with KubernetesProvider\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `_get_k8s_status()` and return Deployment status\n\n#### Scenario: Status for AgentCube CR\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and agent was deployed as AgentRuntime CR\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `_get_cr_k8s_status()` and return CR status\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: StatusRuntime — CR Status Interpretation\n\nThe system SHALL correctly interpret AgentRuntime CR status fields.\n\n#### Scenario: CR has status fields\n- **GIVEN** the CR object has `\"status\"` key with `\"status\"` and `\"agentEndpoint\"` subfields\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` processes it\n- **THEN** it SHALL extract and return these status values\n\n#### Scenario: CR exists but has no status\n- **GIVEN** the CR object exists but lacks a `\"status\"` key\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` processes it\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `status=\"created_no_status\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CR not found in K8s\n- **GIVEN** the CR does not exist in the cluster\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `status=\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Integration — InvokeRuntime Provider Selection\n\nThe system SHALL route invocations through the correct provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke AgentCube provider endpoint\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct endpoint as `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke K8s provider directly\n- **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` or direct endpoint is configured\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL POST to the configured `agent_endpoint` or service URL directly\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling — Kubernetes API Errors\n\nThe system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors gracefully.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes connection failure\n- **GIVEN** the cluster is unreachable\n- **WHEN** any provider method attempts to call Kubernetes API\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., connection error) with descriptive message\n\n#### Scenario: Permission denied\n- **GIVEN** the user lacks RBAC permissions for the operation\n- **WHEN** any provider method is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL propagate the `ApiException` with status 403\n\n#### Scenario: Resource already exists\n- **GIVEN** attempting to create a resource that already exists (and patch is not working)\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent()` or `deploy_agent_runtime()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL handle the conflict appropriately (update existing or raise error)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling — Validation Errors\n\nThe system SHALL validate inputs before calling Kubernetes API.\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid NodePort range\n- **GIVEN** `node_port=29999` (below 30000)\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be in range 30000-32767\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid port number\n- **GIVEN** `port=70000` (exceeds 65535)\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating invalid port number\n\n#### Scenario: Empty agent name\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"\"` or `agent_name=None`\n- **WHEN** provider deployment methods are called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring a valid agent name\n\n#### Scenario: Empty image URL\n- **GIVEN** `image_url=\"\"` or `image_url=None`\n- **WHEN** provider deployment methods are called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring a valid image URL\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Reference\n\n### KubernetesProvider Class\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _create_deployment(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        replicas: int,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _create_service(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        port: int,\n        node_port: Optional[int]\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Class\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package exports |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client for API interactions |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation (via `AgentMetadata`) |\n| `PyYAML>=6.0` | YAML parsing for kubeconfig |\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `PublishRuntime` | Uses `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` or `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` based on `--provider` flag |\n| `StatusRuntime` | Uses `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` or `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` based on provider |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | Uses provider info to construct correct invocation URLs |\n| CLI `publish` command | Passes `--provider`, `--node-port`, `--replicas`, `--namespace` options to providers |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Kubernetes Client:** Use the official `kubernetes` Python client library\n2. **CRD API Group:** AgentRuntime CR uses `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n3. **Resource Naming:** Both providers share `_sanitize_name()` logic for consistency\n4. **Namespace Handling:** Both providers use `_ensure_namespace()` pattern\n5. **Timeout Defaults:** Default deployment wait timeout is 120 seconds\n6. **NodePort Range:** Valid range is 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n7. **Error Propagation:** Kubernetes API exceptions should be caught and wrapped with context\n8. **Verbose Logging:** Both providers support verbose mode for debugging API calls\n9. **Session Defaults:** AgentRuntime uses `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n10. **Image Pull Secrets:** AgentRuntime always includes `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775899709901,"end":1775899709910}}}}
