{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899719129,"sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdf3078001sFDkwRjA6NxzJ8","messageID":"msg_d7bdf120c001BRGE2biVMMHbNg","sessionID":"ses_28424d447ffePQtL9U3b1uD4b3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-026  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n10: \n11: This delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Initialize with default namespace\n22: - **GIVEN** no namespace is provided\n23: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL default `namespace` to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Initialize with custom namespace\n27: - **GIVEN** `namespace=\"my-namespace\"`, `verbose=True`, and `kubeconfig=\"/path/to/kubeconfig\"`\n28: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(...)` is instantiated\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL store these values and configure the Kubernetes client accordingly\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Initialize with kubeconfig from environment\n32: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is `None` and environment variable `KUBECONFIG` is set\n33: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is instantiated\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubernetes client with default configuration (likely from `~/.kube/config` or in-cluster config)\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Verbose logging during initialization\n37: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True`\n38: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider(verbose=True)` is instantiated\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL log initialization details including namespace configuration\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Namespace Management\n44: \n45: The system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before deploying resources.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n48: - **GIVEN** the namespace `\"my-namespace\"` already exists in the cluster\n49: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL not raise an error and continue without creating the namespace again\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Namespace does not exist\n53: - **GIVEN** the namespace `\"new-namespace\"` does not exist in the cluster\n54: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL create the namespace using the Kubernetes API\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Namespace creation failure\n58: - **GIVEN** the user lacks permission to create namespaces\n59: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` attempts to create a namespace\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `ApiException` or permission error)\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Name Sanitization\n65: \n66: The system SHALL sanitize agent names to comply with Kubernetes resource naming conventions.\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Valid name passed through\n69: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my-agent\"`\n70: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my-agent\")` is called\n71: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` unchanged\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Uppercase letters converted to lowercase\n74: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"My-Agent\"`\n75: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"My-Agent\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-agent\"` (lowercase)\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Invalid characters replaced\n79: - **GIVEN** an agent name `\"my_agent@v1.0\"`\n80: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(\"my_agent@v1.0\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL return a sanitized version with invalid characters replaced or removed\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Long names truncated\n84: - **GIVEN** an agent name exceeding 63 characters (Kubernetes DNS label limit)\n85: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name()` is called\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL truncate the name to comply with Kubernetes naming constraints\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Agent Deployment\n91: \n92: The system SHALL deploy agents as Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Deploy agent with minimal configuration\n95: - **GIVEN** `agent_name=\"hello-agent\"`, `image_url=\"hello:v1.0.0\"`, `port=8080`\n96: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port)` is called\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n98:   1. Ensure namespace exists\n99:   2. Create a Deployment with the specified image and port\n100:   3. Create a NodePort Service exposing the port\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 619. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-026  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the Kubernetes provider classes that handle agent deployment to both standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) and AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime CR).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — Initialization and Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide `KubernetesProvider` to interact with Kubernetes clusters for deploying agents using standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775899719118,"end":1775899719126}}}}
